l Group deployed Apical in 12 flagship locations in Q2, then expanded to 38 by year-end. They moved from referring out 42% of implant cases to retaining 89% in-house within a single quarter. Net new implant revenue, year one: $2.41M. Average case margin: 61%.</p></div>","_animation":"fadeInUp","_animation_delay":100}},{"id":"v2pproof_blk1","elType":"widget","widgetType":"text-editor","settings":{"editor":"<div style=\"font-family:Inter;max-width:720px;margin:0 auto;border-top:1px solid rgba(26,26,28,0.14);padding-top:32px\"><div style=\"font-size:11px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:2px;text-transform:uppercase;color:rgba(26,26,28,0.5);margin-bottom:18px\">CASE STUDY 02 — HEARTLAND</div><h3 style=\"font-family:Fraunces;font-size:1.85rem;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:-0.5px;color:#1A1A1C;margin:0 0 18px;line-height:1.15\">3.2x implant cases per day per chair.</h3><p style=\"font-size:1rem;line-height:1.7;color:rgba(26,26,28,0.75);margin:0\">Across 28 pilot locations, Heartland measured a 3.2x increase in implant cases completed per day per equipped chair — from 1.1 to 3.6. Surgical time dropped from 84 to 47 minutes average. Patient NPS for the procedure climbed from 72 to 91.</p></div>","_animation":"fadeInUp","_animation_delay":180}},{"id":"v2pproof_blk2","elType":"widget","widgetType":"text-editor","settings":{"editor":"<div style=\"font-family:Inter;max-width:720px;margin:0 auto;border-top:1px solid rgba(26,26,28,0.14);padding-top:32px\"><div style=\"font-size:11px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:2px;text-transform:uppercase;color:rgba(26,26,28,0.5);margin-bottom:18px\">CASE STUDY 03 — GREAT EXPRESSIONS</div><h3 style=\"font-family:Fraunces;font-size:1.85rem;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:-0.5px;color:#1A1A1C;margin:0 0 18px;line-height:1.15\">From 0 implants to 420/month in six months.</h3><p style=\"font-size:1rem;line-height:1.7;color:rgba(26,26,28,0.75);margin:0\">Great Expressions had never offered in-house implants. With Apical, their general dentists comple